<div id="review_3642184545" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3642184545" />
    <a title="Brian Grover" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16026178-brian-grover"><img alt="Brian Grover" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1362025929p2/16026178.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3642184545?book_show_action=true">Nov 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brian Grover" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brian Grover" href="/user/show/16026178-brian-grover">Brian Grover</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780312680466" href="/book/show/9229338-the-lost-books-of-the-odyssey">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16026178-brian-grover?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16026178-brian-grover?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3642184545" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10922824813350406645">First of all let me say that this was the ultra-rare (for me) &quot;just browsing in a bookstore and randomly pulled a book that looked interesting off a shelf and bought it&quot;. We were visiting some friends up in Kingston, and it was a rainy Saturday so they took us to a local bookstore they like that doubles as a pretty good beer/coffee bar, and we just all tucked in and read/drank for a while. Shout out to Rough Draft Bar &amp; Books!<br/><br/>Anyway, this seemed fun, an ostensible collection of myths that got om</span>
  <span id="freeText10922824813350406645" style="display:none">First of all let me say that this was the ultra-rare (for me) "just browsing in a bookstore and randomly pulled a book that looked interesting off a shelf and bought it". We were visiting some friends up in Kingston, and it was a rainy Saturday so they took us to a local bookstore they like that doubles as a pretty good beer/coffee bar, and we just all tucked in and read/drank for a while. Shout out to Rough Draft Bar &amp; Books!<br /><br />Anyway, this seemed fun, an ostensible collection of myths that got omitted from Homer's version of The Odyssey. Or, I suppose, a collection of stories inspired by The Odyssey, but wildly different in theme and tone. Scylla and Polyphemus are here, but in Mason's telling they're sympathetic characters; Odysseus comes off as a rank villain. His story is spun forwards and back through time, each one of these little vignettes is a blank slate, loosely inspired by the source material.<br /><br />Friends, I LOVED this book. I read it in dribs and drabs, one story every night or two over the course of a few months. Mason is just masterful - his voice is timeless and all-knowing, as any spinner of myths has to be. An absolute delight, and a must for anyone who enjoyed reading/hearing the Greek myths as a child (or an adult, for that matter).</span>
  <a data-text-id="10922824813350406645" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


